### Define a Basic Server Action in Next.js

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/02-guides/single-page-applications.mdx

This code snippet illustrates how to define a simple server action using the `'use server'` directive in Next.js. Server actions run exclusively on the server and can be directly imported and called from client components, removing the need for traditional API endpoints.

```ts
'use server'

export async function create() {}
```

```js
'use server'

export async function create() {}
```

