### Define Server Action with Extra Arguments in Next.js

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/02-guides/forms.mdx

This snippet defines a Next.js Server Action that is designed to accept additional arguments before the standard `FormData` object. The `updateUser` function is marked with `'use server'` and specifies `userId` as its first parameter, allowing it to receive contextual data when invoked via methods like `Function.prototype.bind` from a form's `action` attribute.

```ts
'use server'

export async function updateUser(userId: string, formData: FormData) {}
```

```js
'use server'

export async function updateUser(userId, formData) {}
```

