### Update Next.js Server Action Signature for React useActionState Integration

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/02-guides/forms.mdx

This code illustrates how to modify a Next.js server action function to accept an `initialState` parameter as its first argument. This updated signature is necessary when integrating the server action with React's `useActionState` hook, enabling the server action to receive and potentially modify a state object that will be passed back to the client component.

```tsx
'use server'

import { z } from 'zod'

export async function createUser(initialState: any, formData: FormData) {
  const validatedFields = schema.safeParse({
    email: formData.get('email'),
  })
  // ...
}
```

