### Enable Next.js Server Actions in Next.js 13

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/05-config/01-next-config-js/serverActions.mdx

For Next.js versions older than 14, where Server Actions are not enabled by default, this configuration explicitly activates them. Setting `experimental.serverActions` to `true` enables this feature, which became stable in Next.js 14 and is enabled automatically.

```javascript
/** @type {import('next').NextConfig} */
const config = {
  experimental: {
    serverActions: true,
  },
}

module.exports = config
```

